:<!--Trigger PerformanceE 504015001: Config/Level/Mission/5040150/Act/Act504015001.json-->
:'''Tribbie:''' Ah, Little Gray! You've come to the garden to relax, too? The scenery here is beautiful. '''We''' often come here when feeling overwhelmed.
:<!--Ends the current performance-->
:<!--Open NPC Menu-->
;(If {{Mission|Passage, Reveal the Past Once More|showChapter=0}} has been completed)
:{{DIcon}} I want to chat with you, Tribbie!
::'''Tribbie:''' No problem! What would you like to discuss, Little Gray? Do you want to hear '''our''' song of prophecy again?
::<!--Custom String Trigger: Wait_Option_504059004_84-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_504059004_84-->
::{{DIcon|Talk}} I want to... hear stories of your travels.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504059303-->
:::'''Tribbie:''' Of course! '''We&ast;'''ve traveled the world for thousands of years &mdash; each of us has countless rich and fascinating experiences. What kind of story would you like to hear, Little Gray?
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} I want to hear about Tribbie's experiences.
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504059305-->
::::'''Tribbie:''' '''We'''? '''We''' remember that when '''we''' left Janusopolis, '''we''' still held the spindle of our homeland in our hands.
::::'''Tribbie:''' Back then, *we* were so naive &mdash; thinking that as demigods, *we* could use the spindle to spin threads of destiny and tie our friends together.
::::'''Tribbie:''' But that spindle was lost in war. Our journey wasn't smooth either. Not a single Chrysos Heir was willing to heed '''our''' call. Worse still, there were villains who imprisoned '''us''' in a cell...
::::'''Tribbie:''' Until Cerydra found '''us'''. It was she who united the Chrysos Heirs and turned the prophecy into law.
::::'''Tribbie:''' I wish I could introduce her to you, but alas... that opportunity is long gone.
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} I want to hear about Trinnon's experiences.
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504059311-->
::::'''Tribbie:''' Trinnon is quiet and intellectual. Long ago, when '''we''' left Janusopolis together, she carried a small stone tablet, hoping to convey her knowledge and ideals to all the Chrysos Heirs who answered the call.
::::'''Tribbie:''' At first, she encountered a group of kind-hearted bards who protected her as they traveled across many lands.
::::'''Tribbie:''' However, mortal lives are fragile, and a hundred years later, she was alone again. By that time, she spoke even less than before...
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} I want to hear about Trianne...
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504059315-->
::::'''Tribbie:''' ...Little Gray, there's no need to hesitate. '''We&ast;'''re no longer that sad. '''We&ast;'''ve already held a farewell ceremony for Trianne. If '''we''' don't turn our toes toward the future, Trianne will feel sad &mdash; and even angry.
::::'''Tribbie:''' Back to the topic. Trianne was the bravest among '''us'''. When she first set out, she held a small wooden sword, huffing and puffing as she dreamed of taking down a Titan herself!
::::'''Tribbie:''' Sadly, it didn't go so well. She was chased by several Titankins all the way from Ladon to Epos in a thrilling escape...
::::'''Tribbie:''' But Trianne proudly told '''us''' that it was precisely because of those experiences &mdash; being chased by the Kins and repeatedly forced to use "Century Gate" &mdash; that she became the most skilled gatekeeper among '''us'''!
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Talk}} Master Tribbie, I want to learn how to use the "Century Gate"!
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504059320-->
:::'''Tribbie:''' Ambitious, Little Gray! But it is impossible for ordinary folks to understand how to use the "Century Gate."
:::'''Tribbie:''' ...That being said, you took one look at Oronyx's Miracle and learned how to use it. That should've been equally impossible... Could Tribbie be wrong and you are a genius all along, Little Gray?
:::'''Tribbie:''' Alright, it's decided. '''We''' will teach you how to use the Century Gate! Let's create some miracles!
:::'''Tribbie:''' Little Gray, please call out the "Gate of Infinity" from the bottom of your heart. Feel the wavering of space and listen to the distant murmurs in your ears...
:::'''Tribbie:''' Then, cast out the power that you sense, like it's a net!
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Open!!!
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504059326-->
::::'''Tribbie:''' ...Little Gray, you scared '''us'''! And it doesn't seem that the gate is opened...
::::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_504059331-->
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504059331-->
::::'''Tribbie:''' It seems that learning to use the "Century Gate" is a bit too difficult for you now, Little Gray. But don't be disheartened. You are already amazing! We know that you will become a great hero of Amphoreus even without the power of the "Century Gate"!
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Ha! Space bomb!
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504059328-->
::::'''Tribbie:''' No, no! That's far too violent, Little Gray! It sounds like you want to completely annihilate space itself!
::::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_504059331-->
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504059331-->
::::'''Tribbie:''' It seems that learning to use the "Century Gate" is a bit too difficult for you now, Little Gray. But don't be disheartened. You are already amazing! We know that you will become a great hero of Amphoreus even without the power of the "Century Gate"!
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} I cannot feel it. Shall I use a Space Anchor?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504059330-->
